Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks, stalks discarded) and roughly chop. Finely chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1} and reserve 1 leaf per person. Halve the remaining lettuce lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}. Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto another #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put the @peanut butter{60%g}, @sambal paste{15%g}, @ketjap manis{25%g}, @sugar{1} and half the @Indonesian style spice mix{1%tsp} into a saucepan then whisk together. Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and stir well to combine. Pop on medium-high heat and bring to a boil, stirring continuously. Reduce the heat, then cook until thickened and creamy, ~{2-4%minutes}, stirring often. Remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lime juice. Mix together, then taste and season with @salt{} or more lime juice if needed.

Put the lime zest and remaining Indonesian style spice mix into a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together and add the chicken. Turn to coat evenly. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, carefully lay in the chicken. Cook until golden brown, ~{5-6%minutes} each side. Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a board, cover with #foil{} and rest for ~{2%minutes}.

IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, squeeze the remaining lime juice into another medium bowl and add the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}, @honey{15%g}, peanuts and mint leaves. Mix together.

TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and chopped lettuce to the bowl of dressing, then toss to coat. Pop your burger buns in the oven to warm through for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reheat the satay sauce if needed and spread a spoonful on each side of your buns. Pop a lettuce leaf on the bun base, top with a chicken breast, then finish with the bun lid. Serve the burgers with the baby gem slaw and wedges alongside. Pop the remaining satay sauce into a #small bowl{} for dipping. Enjoy!